-----------------------------------------------------<br>
If you've ever played another MMOG, you'd know that there really aren't such things as &quot;fresh and level playing fields&quot;, largely because the same type of people who turned EverQuest into a race to the finish line are ready to pounce on and exploit the same content of other games. That being said, if you change your focus on what you want out of a game, and realize that if you don't have 12-16 hours a day to dedicate to the early exploitation and conquest of game content to compete with those that do, you'll end up enjoying the game a whole lot more.<br>
