<br>
However, it absolutely astounds me to hear some of the complaints.  Like not being able to start in various cities.  Apparently you, who are complaining, have not read that Norrath has fallen victim to dark forces and undergone massive changes.  Luclin has blown up and thrown all of Norrath into chaos.  I personally think this makes for an interesting story arc.  Let's focus on that rather than whine that you won't get to start in Felwithe or wherever else you think you should start.  Let's talk about the new possibilties rather than whine about what you think you are going to lose.  What we know is that all good-aligned players will begin in Qeynos and all evil-aligned will begin in Freeport.  We know that both cities are now massive.  We know that Freeport is ruled by a new villian and that Qeynos is ruled by Antonia Bale, a female.  We know that the people of this new Norrath have chosen sides.  Which side will you chose?<br>
<br>
Other complaints center on the tradeskill class that makes the best armor/equipment.  Big deal,  see the system work before you condemn it.  Some complain about the &quot;item wear&quot; system.  Again, big deal,  see the system work before you condemn it.<br>
<br>
I look forward to all these new things.  If it turns out that they are bad.  Then I will not play.<br>
<br>
I would just like to see some positive discussion about new possibilities instead of complaining all the time.<br>
